Sentencas: For nano-porous anodized aluminum oxide (AAO) template based low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs), anode structure has crucial effects on electrochemical characteristics because of triple phase boundary densities and electrical connectivity of metal catalysts on porous AAO substrates.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, we investigated effects of fabrication processes of Ni anode for AAO template based LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Ni anodes were prepared at various deposition pressure, i.e. low pressure, high pressure and low pressure-high pressure, on nano-porous AAO substrates by physical vapor deposition.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Surface morphology and cross-sectional structure of various Ni anodes were systematically evaluated.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical characterizations of LT-SOFCs with various anode structures were successfully conducted at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The Ni anode prepared at low pressure showed high electrical conductivity and low catalytic activity.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, Ni anode which was fabricated at high pressure exhibited poor electrical conductivity and good catalytic activity.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Bilayer Ni anode which was deposited in sequence at low pressure and high pressure presented both good electrical conductivity and good catalytic activity.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The LT-SOFC with the bilayer Ni anode cell achieved the best performance, 201 mW/cm(2)at 500 degrees C. Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy analysis was conducted to reveal detailed behaviors of AAO based LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Therefore, we successfully optimized the anode structure for high performance AAO template based LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Effects of Microstructure of Ni Anode on Nanotemplate Based Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
